abstract: A little bit of choice, a whole lot of chaos.
snippet: A little bit of choice, a whole lot of chaos.
lead_paragraph: DAVENPORT, Iowa — “So if you’re with pineapple the first round, and there are enough voters, do pineapples become viable and you can no longer change to blueberries?” a man at the table near me asked.

abstract: The new treaty could be an important lever for long- awaited modernization.
snippet: The new treaty could be an important lever for long- awaited modernization.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — For Mexico, the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement, an updated version of the North American Free Trade Agreement, is certainly better than having President Trump scrap the pact altogether, as he threatened to do in 2017. Beyond the debate about whether the agreement, which was finally approved by Congress recently and is to be signed into law by Mr. Trump today, has more pluses or minuses for Mexico, the real question is whether it can truly become a powerful lever for the country’s long awaited modernization. At a cost, it could.

abstract: Survey results suggests their views and priorities are far more alike than different, despite labels like moderate or progressive, centrist or liberal.
snippet: Survey results suggests their views and priorities are far more alike than different, despite labels like moderate or progressive, centrist or liberal.
lead_paragraph: The four Democratic candidates at the top of the polls heading into the Iowa caucuses have been paired by pundits into what they like to call lanes. It’s a highway analogy, as in “stay in your lane.” One, seen as more progressive and liberal, contains Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren. The other, consisting of Joe Biden and Pete Buttigieg, is more centrist and moderate.

headline_print_headline: Goldman, Trying Something New, Opens Up

abstract: The framework will outline investment over the next five years and provide a foundation for legislation that is currently being drafted or debated in House committees.
snippet: The framework will outline investment over the next five years and provide a foundation for legislation that is currently being drafted or debated in House committees.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats on Wednesday plan to unveil a five-year, $760 billion framework for rebuilding the nation’s highways, airports and other infrastructure, laying out an election-year package with little chance of enactment after bipartisan talks with the White House on the issue failed to gain traction.

abstract: Chinese officials have confirmed over 7,700 cases of the mysterious illness as foreign governments airlifted their citizens out of Wuhan, the outbreak’s epicenter.
snippet: Chinese officials have confirmed over 7,700 cases of the mysterious illness as foreign governments airlifted their citizens out of Wuhan, the outbreak’s epicenter.
lead_paragraph: Mainland China now has more cases of coronavirus than it had of SARS, a respiratory infection that spread across China in 2002 and 2003 and killed 774 people in 17 countries.  During the SARS outbreak, China had 5,327 cases and 349 deaths, according to the World Health Organization.

lead_paragraph: “The message to the Palestinians, boiled down to its essence, is: You’ve lost, get over it.”
headline_main: Quotation of the Day: Two Allies Draw Map With Voters in Mind
